        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Palantir’s stock <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-05-02-2025-surged-24-percent" target="_blank">surged 24%</a> to an all-time high after reporting stronger-than-expected Q4 earnings. The company reported adjusted earnings of $0.14 per share, surpassing expectations of $0.11 per share. The company also raised its guidance for 2025 revenue to $3.74 billion—$3.76 billion. CEO Alex Karp described the demand for the company’s commercial and government segments as unprecedented.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The surge in earnings is largely attributable to Palantir’s aggressive expansion into artificial intelligence with its Artificial Intelligence Platform (AIP). The platform integrates AI with big data analytics to enhance decision-making and increase security. AI-driven defense and intelligence solutions fueled 45% YoY growth in government revenue.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
