            <strong>🇯🇵 Japan to tighten buyout rules to protect minority investors</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Japan’s management buyout (MBOs) boom <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-05-02-2025-faces-stricter-oversight" target="_blank">faces stricter oversight</a> as the Tokyo Stock Exchange considers new regulations to protect shareholders. Companies would be required to disclose price calculations for buyouts as per the proposed amendments.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Last year saw the highest number of MBOs since 2011. However, activist investors like Oasis Management have increasingly started to challenge low-priced buyouts. The new regulations will prevent companies from going private at artificially low prices.
          </p>
