            <strong>🇬🇧 UK banknote printer weighs takeover bids</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          British banknote printer De la Rue Plc has received a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-05-02-2025-premilinary-takeover" target="_blank">preliminary takeover</a> offer from Disruptive Capital and Pension SuperFund Capital. The cash offer of $1.30 per share represents a 22% premium.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Established in 1813, the banknote printer has struggled with declining demand of late for physical currency as digital and contactless payments become more widespread. The company has been undergoing restructuring involving selling non-core assets. De La Rue’s stock surged 14% on the takeover news, its largest intraday gain in nearly three months.
        </p>
