              margin-top: 2px !important;">What are Green Swan events?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/john-elkington-green-swan-events.png" alt="John Elkington The Father Of Green Swan Events" href="https://www.longandshort.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            John Elkington delivers a speech at a conference. Credits: LGT
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000"> 
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"><a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-05-02-2025-green-swan" target="_blank">Green Swan</a> events are <strong>highly disruptive events</strong> that take society towards better outcomes. Unlike <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-05-02-2025-black-swan-event" target="_blank">Black Swan events</a>, Green Swan events are <strong>foreseeable</strong> as they are driven by climate change.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          John Elkington originated the term. He says Green Swans are “<strong>solutions that take us exponentially toward breakthroughs</strong>.” The economic impact of green swan events can cause cascading effects for several industries.
         </p>
         <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"><strong>Example: European heatwave and wildfires (2022–2023)</strong>
         </p>
         <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Europe experienced <strong>extreme heatwaves and wildfires</strong> in 2022 and 2023, with temperatures exceeding 40°C. The crisis was worsened by low water levels in Rhine and Danube. This led to poor wheat and crop harvest the following year, <strong>increasing food prices</strong>. Moreover, supply chains were disrupted due to low water levels, which affected moving goods.
         </p>
        </mj-text>
